<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="179" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1436,150,393]" pageId="24" pageNumber="179">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,294,320]" pageId="24" pageNumber="179">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons with median carina present but weakly marked. Lateral carinae of the frons, above lateral ocellus, yellow for a long distance, extended beyond half the height of the eye. Pronotum with median longitudinal carina absent. Periandrium bearing one spine and aedeagus with two spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
