<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="180" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,150,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Description</emphasis>
: Coloration. General body color dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[858,991,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–99" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-66@23.[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 95–99. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.,: 95. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 96. Habitus, dorsal view; 97. Male head, anterior view; 98. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 99. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 95–96 = 0.5 mm; 97, 99= 0.2 mm; 98= 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405051/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Figs 95–96</figureCitation>
). Lateral carinae of the frons above lateral ocelli, vertex, median region of pronotum and mesonotum, epimeron and episternum yellow. Forewing brown, darker on basal half, with white regions: oval spot in the median region of the costal cell, C2 and C5’ cells predominantly white, C3 cell with a horizontal narrow strip, at the apex of the cubital cell, on the postclaval margin, and at the apex of the clavus (
<figureCitation box="[410,508,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 126–133. Wings of Bennarella species. 126. Bennarella bicoloripennis Muir; 127. Bennarella fusca Muir; 128. Bennarella guidai sp. nov.; 129. Bennarella henriquesi sp. nov.; 130. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.; 131. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.; 132. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.; 133. Bennarella xavieri sp. nov.. Abbreviations: A1, first anal vein; A2, second anal vein; CuA1; CuA2; CuP, Cubitus posterior; MP1, first media posterior branch; MP2, second media posterior branch; MP3, third media posterior branch; MP4, fourth media posterior branch; MP5, fifth media posterior branch; Pcu+A1, Postcubitus+first anal vein; Pcu, Postcubitus; RA, radius anterior branch; RP1, first radius posterior branch; RP2, second radius posterior branch; ScP, Subcosta posterior. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405067/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma brown. Hindwing semihyaline, light brown. Legs dark brown (coloration observed in the 
<typeStatus box="[392,494,331,357]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">paratype</typeStatus>
). Upper half of sternite III, dorsal region of sternite IV and V yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1276,1406,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–99" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-66@23.[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 95–99. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.,: 95. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 96. Habitus, dorsal view; 97. Male head, anterior view; 98. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 99. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 95–96 = 0.5 mm; 97, 99= 0.2 mm; 98= 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405051/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Figs 95, 99</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">
Head: frons with median carina present, but weakly marked; lateral carina of frons weakly directed obliquely laterally (
<figureCitation box="[260,347,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–99" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-66@23.[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 95–99. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.,: 95. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 96. Habitus, dorsal view; 97. Male head, anterior view; 98. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 99. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 95–96 = 0.5 mm; 97, 99= 0.2 mm; 98= 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405051/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
); vertex length approximately half the median length of the pronotum in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1423,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–99" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-66@23.[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 95–99. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.,: 95. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 96. Habitus, dorsal view; 97. Male head, anterior view; 98. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 99. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 95–96 = 0.5 mm; 97, 99= 0.2 mm; 98= 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405051/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
); pedicel approximately 5 times longer than wide and scape conspicuous (
<figureCitation box="[975,1061,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–99" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-66@23.[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 95–99. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.,: 95. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 96. Habitus, dorsal view; 97. Male head, anterior view; 98. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 99. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 95–96 = 0.5 mm; 97, 99= 0.2 mm; 98= 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405051/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
). Thorax: pronotum with median longitudinal carina absent; mesonotum with median and lateral longitudinal carinae present, but weakly marked (
<figureCitation box="[160,244,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–99" captionStartId="23.[151,264,1913,1937]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-66@23.[151,1435,417,1889]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 95–99. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.,: 95. Holotype male habitus, lateral view; 96. Habitus, dorsal view; 97. Male head, anterior view; 98. Male head and thorax, dorsal view; 99. Male abdominal process, lateral view. Scale bars: 95–96 = 0.5 mm; 97, 99= 0.2 mm; 98= 0.3 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405051" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405051/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
). Forewing: m-cu cross-vein present (
<figureCitation box="[669,767,510,536]" captionStart="FIGURES 126–133" captionStartId="29.[151,264,1521,1545]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-17@29.[151,1435,181,1497]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 126–133. Wings of Bennarella species. 126. Bennarella bicoloripennis Muir; 127. Bennarella fusca Muir; 128. Bennarella guidai sp. nov.; 129. Bennarella henriquesi sp. nov.; 130. Bennarella maculipennis sp. nov.; 131. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov.; 132. Bennarella vittata sp. nov.; 133. Bennarella xavieri sp. nov.. Abbreviations: A1, first anal vein; A2, second anal vein; CuA1; CuA2; CuP, Cubitus posterior; MP1, first media posterior branch; MP2, second media posterior branch; MP3, third media posterior branch; MP4, fourth media posterior branch; MP5, fifth media posterior branch; Pcu+A1, Postcubitus+first anal vein; Pcu, Postcubitus; RA, radius anterior branch; RP1, first radius posterior branch; RP2, second radius posterior branch; ScP, Subcosta posterior. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405067" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405067/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 132</figureCitation>
). Legs: hind tibia with 6 apical spines; hind tarsus with 7+7 apical spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[398,560,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURES 100–106" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,417,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-103@24.[151,1435,417,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 100–106. Bennarella vittata sp. nov., male genitalia: 100. Genital capsule, lateral view; 101. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 102. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 103. Gonostylus rigth lateral view; 104. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 105. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 106. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 100, 102 = 0.2 mm; 101, 103–106 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405053/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Figs 100–106</figureCitation>
). Pygofer subtriangular in lateral view, posterior margin without projections (
<figureCitation box="[160,258,618,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 100–106" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,417,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-103@24.[151,1435,417,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 100–106. Bennarella vittata sp. nov., male genitalia: 100. Genital capsule, lateral view; 101. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 102. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 103. Gonostylus rigth lateral view; 104. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 105. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 106. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 100, 102 = 0.2 mm; 101, 103–106 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405053/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
); medioventral process of pygofer conspicuous in lateral view, with posterior margin triangular in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[222,322,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 100–106" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,417,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-103@24.[151,1435,417,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 100–106. Bennarella vittata sp. nov., male genitalia: 100. Genital capsule, lateral view; 101. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 102. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 103. Gonostylus rigth lateral view; 104. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 105. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 106. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 100, 102 = 0.2 mm; 101, 103–106 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405053/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 100</figureCitation>
). Gonostyli with pointed apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[852,951,654,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 100–106" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,417,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-103@24.[151,1435,417,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 100–106. Bennarella vittata sp. nov., male genitalia: 100. Genital capsule, lateral view; 101. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 102. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 103. Gonostylus rigth lateral view; 104. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 105. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 106. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 100, 102 = 0.2 mm; 101, 103–106 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405053/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
); narrowed at basal two third, wider in the apical third and divergent apically in dorsal and posterior views (
<figureCitation box="[890,1048,690,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 100–106" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,417,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-103@24.[151,1435,417,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 100–106. Bennarella vittata sp. nov., male genitalia: 100. Genital capsule, lateral view; 101. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 102. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 103. Gonostylus rigth lateral view; 104. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 105. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 106. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 100, 102 = 0.2 mm; 101, 103–106 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405053/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Figs 102, 104</figureCitation>
) Phallic complex (
<figureCitation box="[1263,1424,690,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 100–106" captionStartId="24.[151,264,1879,1903]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,417,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-103@24.[151,1435,417,1856]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 100–106. Bennarella vittata sp. nov., male genitalia: 100. Genital capsule, lateral view; 101. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 102. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 103. Gonostylus rigth lateral view; 104. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 105. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 106. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 100, 102 = 0.2 mm; 101, 103–106 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405053" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405053/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Figs 105–106</figureCitation>
): periandrium almost straight with one long, slender and sinuous spine, inserted at median region (S1); aedeagus slender with bifid apex divided into a curved and an almost straight tip, and two spines: one short spine inserted near base (S2), and one long straight spine, inserted in the median region (S3). Anal tube concave in ventral view; base of the anal tube approximately 0.6 times the length of anal tube extension in lateral view; anal tube extension expanded ventrally, with apex smoothly reentrant in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[916,1047,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURES 88–94" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-24@22.[151,1435,181,1844]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 88–94. Bennarella rafaeli sp. nov., male genitalia: 88. Genital capsule, lateral view; 89. Anal tube and pygofer, dorsal view; 90. Anal tube, pygofer and gonostyli, posterior view; 91. Gonostylus left lateral view; 92. Gonostyli, dorsal view; 93. Phallic complex, left lateral view; 94. Phallic complex, right lateral view. Scale bars: 88, 90 = 0.2 mm; 89, 91–94 = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405049" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405049/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Figs 88–90</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="180" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,150,1041]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,906,932]" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[517,579,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="180">vittae</emphasis>
, stripe. The species name is allusive to a yellow stripe that extends from the vertex to the apex of the clavus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
